          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-02-11 11:33:27" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of σκανδαλίζομαι ‘to fall into a trap,’ not occurring in the NT) to give up believing what is right and let oneself believe what is false</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to cease believing</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to give up believing</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is also possible to understand σκανδαλίζομαι in {S:04001302100038} as meaning ‘to let oneself be led into sin’ or ‘to fall into sin as the result of unbelief.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
